{"word":"ἀμφιχέω","slug":"ἀμφιχέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀμφιχέω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to pour around, to pour</i> or <i>spread over</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be poured</i> or <i>shed around</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of persons, <i>to embrace</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}